{
  "text_id": "oracc.etcsri.Q001133",
  "corpus": "oracc",
  "title": "URU-KA-gina 05 (RIME 1.09.09.05 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q001133",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(o i 1) The leader of Umma set fire to boundary levees ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.4",
      "line_range": "4",
      "translation": "(o i 4) He set fire to the Antasura . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.8",
      "line_range": "8",
      "translation": "(o i 8) He looted the great temple of Tiraš ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.10",
      "line_range": "10",
      "translation": "(o i 10) He looted the Abzu-banda ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.12",
      "line_range": "12",
      "translation": "(o i 12) He looted the pedestal of Enlil and the pedestal of Utu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.15",
      "line_range": "15",
      "translation": "(o ii 2) He looted the Ahuš . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.19",
      "line_range": "19",
      "translation": "(o ii 6) He looted the E-babbar . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.23",
      "line_range": "23",
      "translation": "(o ii 10) He looted the high temple of Ninmah in Tirkug . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.29",
      "line_range": "29",
      "translation": "(o iii 3) He looted the Bagara . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.33",
      "line_range": "33",
      "translation": "(o iii 7) He set fire to the Dugru . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(o iii 11) He looted the Abzu-ega ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.39",
      "line_range": "39",
      "translation": "(o iii 13) He set fire to the temple of Ĝatumdug . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli . He destroyed all its statues ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.45",
      "line_range": "45",
      "translation": "(o iv 5) He set fire to Inana’s oval E-ana . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli . He destroyed all its statues ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.50",
      "line_range": "50",
      "translation": "(o iv 10) He looted the Šagepada . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.55",
      "line_range": "55",
      "translation": "(o v 1) In Henda he tore down all the canopies ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.57",
      "line_range": "57",
      "translation": "(o v 3) In Kieša , he looted the temple of Nindara . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.62",
      "line_range": "62",
      "translation": "(o v 8) In Kinunir , he set fire to the temple of Dumzid-abzu . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.67",
      "line_range": "67",
      "translation": "(r i 2) He set fire to the temple of Lugal-Uruba . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.71",
      "line_range": "71",
      "translation": "(r i 6) He looted the E-engura of Nanše . He seized all its precious metal and lapis lazuli ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.76",
      "line_range": "76",
      "translation": "(r i 11) In Saĝub , he looted the temple of Ama-ĝeštin . He seized all her precious metal and lapis lazuli from ( the statue of ) Ama-ĝeštin , and threw ( the statue ) in ( the temple’s ) well ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.83",
      "line_range": "83",
      "translation": "(r ii 7) He tore out the barley of all the cultivated fields of Ninĝirsu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001133.86",
      "line_range": "86",
      "translation": "(r ii 10) Having raided Lagaš , the leader of Umma surely committed a sin against Ninĝirsu ! He raised a hand against him , ( and that hand ) must be cut off ! Iri-kagina , the king of Ĝirsu , is not capable of punishment . May Nisaba , the personal god of Lugal-zage-si , the ruler of Umma , take the responsibility for the punishment !"
    }
  ],
